SIMPLE: suspicious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suspicious
<hw>Sus*pi"cious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>suspecious</ets>; cf. L. <ets>suspiciosus</ets>. See
<er>Suspicion</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Inclined to suspect; given
or prone to suspicion; apt to imagine without proof.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nature itself, after it has done an injury, will ever be
<qex>suspicious</qex>; and no man can love the person he suspects.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Many mischievous insects are daily at work to make men of merit
<qex>suspicious</qex> of each other.</q> <rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Indicating suspicion, mistrust, or fear.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We have a <qex>suspicious</qex>, fearful, constrained
countenance.</q> <rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Liable to suspicion; adapted to raise suspicion;
giving reason to imagine ill; questionable; <as>as, an author of
<ex>suspicious</ex> innovations; <ex>suspicious</ex>
circumstances</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I spy a black, <qex>suspicious</qex>, threatening could.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Jealous; distrustful; mistrustful; doubtful;
questionable. See <er>Jealous</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sus*pi"cious*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sus*pi"cious*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suspiral</ent>⟦br⟧
